text: Cimarron County is a county in the U.S. state of Oklahoma. The 2020 census shows it has the least people of any county in Oklahoma. As of 2020, 2,296 people lived there. Its county seat is Boise City. == History == Cimarron County was made in 1907. == Geography == The county has a total area of 1,841 square miles. == References == Category:Oklahoma counties Category:1907 establishments in Oklahoma
title: Cimarron County, Oklahoma
